<BaseLayout
  title="About Veralix Research"
  description="Learn about Veralix Research, our methodology, and the market verticals we cover."
  canonicalPath="/about"
>
  <section class="about-page">
    <div class="about-page__inner">
      <h1>About Veralix Research</h1>
      <p>
        Veralix Research is an independent market intelligence firm focused on helping investors, operators, and
        corporate strategy teams understand how competitive markets are evolving beneath headline narratives. Our work
        combines primary interviews, provider benchmarking, budget analysis, and sector mapping to identify the
        commercial forces that influence category expansion, buyer behavior, and platform adoption.
      </p>
      <p>
        We specialize in research that moves beyond surface-level trend commentary. Each report is designed to show how
        structural changes in spending, regulation, technology adoption, and go-to-market execution affect the outlook
        for vendors and the priorities of enterprise buyers. The result is a body of work intended for readers who need
        clarity, evidence, and context before making strategic commitments.
      </p>

      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>Our Methodology</h2>
        <p>
          Our methodology combines qualitative and quantitative inputs into a consistent research framework. We evaluate
          provider positioning, product depth, customer economics, procurement cycles, and the external factors that
          shape category momentum. Research conclusions are formed through source triangulation rather than a single
          dataset, allowing us to test assumptions across interviews, industry disclosures, partner commentary, and
          observed demand signals.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>Research Verticals</h2>
        <ul class="vertical-list">
          <li>Cybersecurity platforms and managed security services</li>
          <li>Financial technology infrastructure and embedded finance</li>
          <li>Cloud software and enterprise application strategy</li>
          <li>Data platforms, analytics, and AI infrastructure</li>
          <li>Healthcare technology and digital care operations</li>
          <li>Industrial automation and connected systems</li>
          <li>Supply chain software and logistics technology</li>
          <li>Payments, banking modernization, and compliance technology</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
